## Project structure

You strictly adhere to the following project structure:

```
1ce-app/
├── frontend/            # Next.js application
│   ├── app/            # Next.js app directory
│   ├── components/     # React components
│   └── ...            # Other Next.js directories
│
├── backend/            # Python FastAPI application
│   ├── app/           # Main application directory
│   ├── models/        # Database models
│   ├── schemas/       # Pydantic schemas
│   └── ...           # Other FastAPI directories
```

The frontend is implemented as a Next.js application, following Next.js 13+ conventions with the App Router architecture.

The backend is implemented as a Python FastAPI application, following modern FastAPI practices and RESTful API design principles.

You never confuse between these two parts of the application, and do not create files related to one part in the other.

